					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2076208#post-2733736</guid>
				<title>Which is the real ending? Vote now on your phone!</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2076208/decisions-we-make#post-2733736</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 25 Jan 2017 20:06:51 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Jacob Conwell</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1372582</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Alright. This is a tale I got inspiration to write pretty quickly after finishing <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/no-good-deed">No Good Deed</a>. I got a little burnt out on action intensive tales like <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/bal-chatri">Bal Chatri</a> and sad, sad tales like <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/all-hallows">All Hallows</a> and wanted to do something a little lower key and a little sweet that featured a bunch of my cast of characters from around the wiki. It’s a little sappy, sure, but it’s a tale I wanted to tell.</p> <p>Originally the tale was going to end on a cliffhanger, with Merlo going into Holman’s office and informing him that she made her decision, but that didn’t pay off to a fair amount of readers. However, I liked the ambiguity of that ending a lot, and rather than back Merlo into a corner by making one ending canon (for now) I decided to include both outcomes. Feel free to let me know which is your favorite.</p> <p>The lyrics featured in this tale are from <em>Ocean Breathes Salty</em> and <em>The View</em>, respectively. Both are songs by the band Modest Mouse.</p> <p>Special thanks to A Random Day, Taffeta, Greenwolf, TwistedGears, Apoplexic, TyGently, Sirens, minmin, AbesntmindedNihilist, Lex1nat0r, Decibelle, Zyn, Randomini, djkaktus, and ProcyonLotor for all their feedback.</p> <p>Extra special thanks to TwistedGears for letting me use his character, Agent Daniel Navarro, yet again.</p> <p>Enjoy the tale.</p> <p><em>JC</em></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
